{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\n\nB-RETIRE removed bespoke orchestrator.run_review, the ONLY producer of the per-pass latency/cost metrics (db7b AC5: coverage['metrics'] = {det_ms, llm_ms, total_ms, llm_calls, claim_path}). The workflow plan-review path did not emit them, so coverage['metrics'] was absent on the workflow gate (the sidecar emitted {}). This is a passive-observability regression (the metrics fed passive latency/cost-target refinement from dogfood data).\n\n## Approach (decided)\n\nCapture the latency split from **recorder step timings**: the workflow interpreter records a per-step `duration_ms` (leaf steps + the batch finder), and `gate_dispatch.produce_plan_review_verdict` reconstructs coverage['metrics'] from rec.steps after the run, attaching it to the verdict. Source decision (resolving the AC's two candidates): step timings for the tier split; the finder step's `criteria_count` for the llm_calls cost proxy.\n\n- **det_ms** = wall-clock of the deterministic floor (the `precheck` step).\n- **llm_ms** = wall-clock of the billable LLM tier (steps of kind agent/batch: Pass-1 finders + Pass-2 verify + Pass-4 coach).\n- **total_ms** = the whole run's wall-clock, measured around run_workflow.\n- **llm_calls** = cost proxy: finder criteria_count + one per succeeded agent step (verify/coach).\n- **claim_path** = the structural marker (the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify; LLM/network-free) — RETAINED, matching the db7b dict exactly.\n\nTolerant of partial/untimed records (a missing duration contributes 0) so it never raises inside the gate, and attached on BOTH the happy path and the coach-failure recovery path.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The workflow interpreter records a per-step `duration_ms` on leaf + batch steps (the recorder step-timing source).\n- [ ] The workflow plan-review path emits coverage['metrics'] = {det_ms, llm_ms, total_ms, llm_calls, claim_path} (incl. claim_path), reconstructed from the workflow run's recorder step timings + the finder criteria_count.\n- [ ] The sidecar carries the metrics again on the workflow gate (lifted to the top level) — verified to equal coverage['metrics'].\n- [ ] A test drives produce_plan_review_verdict end-to-end OFFLINE and asserts the metrics are produced AND plausible (all five keys present; det_ms/llm_ms >= 0; total_ms >= llm_ms; llm_calls > 0; claim_path is the structural marker)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782546054261942001,"uuid":"34125e16-7d19-4b70-a2c0-a328fa37e5ef"}